Over 5,000 security volunteers will be insourced by rail agency Prasa, to protect railway infrastructure in Gauteng. The volunteers will receive security and safety skills training for railway services. eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu reports. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Over 5,000 security volunteers will be insourced by rail agency Prasa to protect railway infrastructure in Gauteng. Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula along with board chairperson Leonard Ramatlakane launched the 'people's responsibility to protect' programme on Monday. READ: Prasa recruits community members for safety initiative The volunteers will receive security and safety skills training for railway services. * eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu reports.